    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!), then add it to a pot with your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, transfer it to a plate and spread it out flat to help it cool down \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely into rounds</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>pineapple</strong>,<strong> </strong>reserving the<strong> pineapple juice</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 1 tbsp per person <strong>pineapple juice</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>gluten free soy sauce </strong>and<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy)</p><p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>pineapple</strong> <strong>glaze</strong></p><p>Add one <strong>pineapple ring</strong> per person (save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>to the pineapple glaze</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>glazed pineapple rings </strong>(reserving the glaze) to the pan and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until lightly charred</p><p>Once lightly charred, add your<strong> cashew nuts </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min or until lightly toasted \u2013 this is your <strong>charred pineapple & cashew nuts</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly toasted, transfer the <strong>charred pineapple & cashew nuts</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Chop the<strong> remaining pineapple</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> grated carrot</strong>,<strong> halved green beans </strong>and <strong>chopped pineapple</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the veg has softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>curry powder </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cooled coconut rice</strong>, the<strong> reserved</strong> <strong>pineapple</strong> <strong>glaze </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until the rice is warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>fried rice</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime[s]</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/charred-pineapple-fried-rice-with-toasted-cashews/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>charred pineapple</strong> on top of the <strong>fried rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped spring onion</strong>, <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>toasted cashew nuts</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
